race.comment: GALACTIC SPARTAN (4) missed the frame last time but before that recorded the quickest win (34.36) on the program at Sandown in a Grade 4/5. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. TAMMY MCIVOR (8) was safely held last time finishing a 9 length fifth at Healesville (19.76) but back to the scene of her latest victory. Has ability and can atone. COPPER RUSH (6) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at The Meadows behind Mepunga Lara (42.90) in a Grade 4/5. Has the pace to be prominent. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Expected to be in this for a long way. MOONLIGHT MILLER (3) has definite claims at his first try at this circuit.
